Welcome!

Thanks for taking this survey. This is part of a research project set up by students at UC Berkeley. We will not be collecting any identifying data about you (such as name, email or address).

The purpose of this survey is to understand transportation mode choice in Berkeley. It will take you 5-10 minutes to complete it.

There is no financial (or otherwise) incentive for you to participate. Taking part is voluntary and you may leave the survey at any point.

If you wish to take part, please confirm that:
- You are aged 18 or above.
- You understand the above information.
- You consent to these terms.
Intro:
Think about your previous experiences traveling in Berkeley and Oakland. In particular, think about a time when you have travelled between two locations that are relatively far apart (30+ min walk).

Q26:
In the following screens, you'll be asked to think about the same journey that you have thought about before, under the same circumstances.

You will now you have to choose between traveling between these two locations on a hypothetical bus or ridehail journey. Bear in mind that the prices and travel times might not exactly match what you have experienced before. Three attributes will be displayed:
- Travel time (min)
- Wait time (min)
- Travel cost ($)

The bus journey will always take 30 minutes and you will have to wait for 12 minutes for the bus. The attributes for the ridehail journey will vary by situation.

Assume that the bus ride will be free (included in your student Clipper card) and that there won't be any extra travel time after the bus drops you at your location (i.e. think of both modes as door to door).
